OL,3,CMum's bid to find missing son who
OL,4,Cvanished on Italian island
OL,6,FThe family believe he was suffering
OL,7,Ffrom heat stroke and say he was in
OL,8,Fsound mind when he left his relatives
OL,9,Fin Sardinia - and in communication
OL,10,Fwith his mother and brother.
OL,12,FCristina said: "I just hope he is with
OL,13,Fsomeone who is looking after him, even
OL,14,Fif they don't know who he is. Michael
OL,15,Fdoesn't have his phone or ID with him,
OL,16,Fhe may well be in a confused state."
OL,18,FA FCDO spokesperson said: "We are
OL,19,Fsupporting the family of a British man
OL,20,Freported missing in Sardinia and are
OL,21,Fin contact with the local authorities".
